<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,1634,2008]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
Frustules rectangular in girdle view, quite broad. Valves broadly rhombic-lanceolate, with cuneate valve ends that are not protracted. Valve length 29.0–43.0 µm, breadth 8.0– 
<quantity box="[902,1002,1673,1699]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="mm" value="10.5">10.5 µm</quantity>
. Axial area narrow-linear, expanding into a narrow-lanceolate, apically elongated central area. Plate-like structure present at the central area, following its shape, crossing the striae (
<figureCitation box="[633,806,1750,1776]" captionStart="FIGURES 365–392" captionStartId="48.[151,271,1806,1830]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,194,1782]" captionTargetId="figure-74@48.[264,1323,194,1782]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="FIGURES 365–392: LM micrographs. Figs 365–372. Hippodonta pulchra (type material). Figs 366, 367. Images of same valve at different focus. Fig. 372. Complete frustule in girdle view. Figs 373–376. Hippodonta costuloides. Fig. 373. Image of broken initial cell. Figs 377–392. Hippodonta intermedia. Fig. 380. Complete frustule in girdle view. Scale bar = 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5072002" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5072002/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Figs 367–371</figureCitation>
). Terminal area weakly distinguishable, quite small. Raphe linear, weakly lateral, with distinct, teardrop-shaped and distantly positioned central pores. Terminal pores of raphe distinct, equally pronounced as the central pores, teardrop-shaped and clearly advancing into the terminal area. Striae coarse, moderately to strongly radiate at the middle, becoming strongly convergent near valve ends, 
<quantity box="[352,457,1905,1931]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.302" metricValueMax="3.556" metricValueMin="3.048" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="in" value="13.0" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="12.0">12–14 in</quantity>
<quantity box="[466,546,1905,1931]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 µm</quantity>
. Interstriae of lower width than the striae, equally pronounced throughout. Lineolae composing the striae quite densely spaced within a stria, rarely discernible with LM, 5–7 within a stria at the middle of the valve.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,151,603]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,351,151,177]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Distribution</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Pavlov, Levkov, D. M. Williams &amp; Edlund" authorityYear="2013" box="[388,628,152,177]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Hippodonta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="pulchra">
<emphasis box="[388,628,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Hippodonta pulchra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has so far only been observed in Lake Baikal, 
<collectingCountry box="[1196,1278,152,178]" name="Russia" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Russia</collectingCountry>
. This species was observed within the sediment of the lake littoral at shallow depth (
<quantity box="[1026,1078,190,216]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" unit="m" value="5.0">5 m</quantity>
). Few other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lange-Bert., Witkowski &amp; Metzeltin" authorityYear="1996" box="[1232,1377,191,216]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Hippodonta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1232,1377,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Hippodonta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
taxa appear at the same locality, namely 
<taxonomicName box="[581,752,229,255]" genus="Navicula" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species" species="costuloides">
<emphasis box="[581,602,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[618,752,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">costuloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Skab.) Kulikovskiy, Metzeltin" authorityName="Kulikovskiy, Metzeltin" baseAuthorityName="Skab." box="[768,1311,229,255]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Hippodonta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis box="[768,789,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[805,934,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">intermedia</emphasis>
(Skab.) Kulikovskiy, Metzeltin
</taxonomicName>
&amp; Lange- Bert. in 
<bibRefCitation author="Kulikovskiy, M. &amp; Lange-Bertalot, H. &amp; Metzeltin D. &amp; Witkowski, A." box="[253,624,268,294]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="1 - 607" refId="ref27477" refString="Kulikovskiy, M., Lange-Bertalot, H., Metzeltin D. &amp; Witkowski, A. (2012) Lake Baikal: Hotspot of endemic diatoms, I. Iconographia Diatomologica 23: 1 - 607." type="journal article" year="2012">
Kulikovskiy 
<emphasis box="[414,477,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">et al.</emphasis>
(2012: 148
</bibRefCitation>
, figs 66: 4–10) (≡ 
<taxonomicName authority="Skab." authorityName="Skab." box="[859,1383,268,294]" genus="Navicula" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="variety" species="hungarica" variety="intermedia">
<emphasis box="[859,1104,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Navicula hungarica</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1168,1301,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">intermedia</emphasis>
Skab.
</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Hippodonta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="microcostulata">
<emphasis box="[1407,1428,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,330,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">microcostulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kulikovskiy, Lange-Bert. &amp; Metzeltin" authorityName="Kulikovskiy, Lange-Bert. &amp; Metzeltin" box="[390,1031,306,332]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Hippodonta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="subelegans">
<emphasis box="[390,411,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[427,560,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">subelegans</emphasis>
Kulikovskiy, Lange-Bert. &amp; Metzeltin
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Kulikovskiy, M. &amp; Lange-Bertalot, H. &amp; Metzeltin D. &amp; Witkowski, A." box="[1071,1431,306,332]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="1 - 607" refId="ref27477" refString="Kulikovskiy, M., Lange-Bertalot, H., Metzeltin D. &amp; Witkowski, A. (2012) Lake Baikal: Hotspot of endemic diatoms, I. Iconographia Diatomologica 23: 1 - 607." type="journal article" year="2012">
Kulikovskiy 
<emphasis box="[1227,1288,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">et al.</emphasis>
(2012: 156
</bibRefCitation>
, 157, figs 67: 26–29), with the latter two being of higher abundance.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,151,603]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,364,383,409]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Observations</emphasis>
:—A combination of characters including the coarsely structured, broad and densely spaced striae, remarkably narrow interstriae, and the presence of a clearly observable plate-like structure at the centre of the valve that crosses the striae, make 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Pavlov, Levkov, D. M. Williams &amp; Edlund" authorityYear="2013" box="[658,790,461,487]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Hippodonta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="pulchra">
<emphasis box="[658,679,461,486]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[696,790,461,486]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">pulchra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
readily distinguishable from other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lange-Bert., Witkowski &amp; Metzeltin" authorityYear="1996" box="[1224,1369,461,486]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Hippodonta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1224,1369,461,486]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Hippodonta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
taxa. Nonetheless, specimens of shorter cell sizes of 
<taxonomicName box="[716,931,500,526]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Hippodonta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="lueneburgensis">
<emphasis box="[716,737,500,525]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[753,931,500,525]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">lueneburgensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appear slightly similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Pavlov, Levkov, D. M. Williams &amp; Edlund" authorityYear="2013" box="[1246,1375,500,526]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Hippodonta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="pulchra">
<emphasis box="[1246,1267,500,525]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1283,1375,500,525]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">pulchra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with regard to the valve outline. However, the remarkably broad striae, the transverse rectangular central area and absence of additional structures in the central area of 
<taxonomicName box="[776,988,577,603]" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Naviculaceae" genus="Hippodonta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Naviculales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="lueneburgensis">
<emphasis box="[776,797,577,602]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[812,988,577,602]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">lueneburgensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
make the two taxa clearly distinct.
</paragraph>
